                                            <p><b>On-Demand Self-Learning:</b></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Learn at your own pace, anytime and wherever you choose&nbsp; and take advantage of the nearly unlimited educational opportunities that come with lifelong access. When you need to refresh ideas or clear your questions, you'll have access to the whole courseware as well as all of the features of our immersive learning experience platform.<br></li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-4-2">2. Who are the instructors?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-4-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-4">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>All of KnowledgeHut’s <b>ITIL Foundation Certification online training</b> is delivered by experienced accredited experts who are:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Masters in ITIL and have immense experience in leading, applying, coaching, and teaching it </li>
                                                <li>Skilled in ITSM</li>
                                                <li>Industry practitioners active in IT operations and the field of IT management. &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Our committed staff of trainers provides training that meets or exceeds the AXELOS level of excellence. Every candidate receives the same high-quality content irrespective of the trainer and the location.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-4-3">3. How different is the ITIL certification online training from the conventional in-person training?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-4-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-4">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Previously, the traditional in-person<b> ITIL certification training</b> was a 16-hour, 2-day training event. The <b>ITIL certification online training</b> has been extended to 14-16 hours.<br></p>
                                            <p>Unlike an in-person session, which features two classes that are typically 7 to 8 hours long, the online <b>ITIL classes</b> for the course are separated into multiple shorter sections. The teacher will communicate with the participants via equipment such as a camera, and participants will be able to digitally work with one another.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-4-4">4. How are the workshops structured?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-4-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-4">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>To give you a fully immersive learning experience, our courses are divided into three parts: pre-workshop, workshop, and post-workshop. Thousands of ITSM professionals we've helped upskill have found our tried-and-true workshop structure to be effective.</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Pre-workshop:</b> Before the workshop, take our diagnostic evaluation to measure your ability levels and set a standard for the rest of the course. This allows you to map and demonstrate your skills learning progression as you reach the end of the course.</li>
                                                <li><b>Workshop: </b>Participate in live and interactive instructor-led sessions directly from PRISM, our immersive learning experience platform with a cutting-edge intelligent coding environment. With projects, evaluations, memory quizzes, simulated examinations, and more, immerse yourself in learning.<br></li>
                                                <li><b>Post-workshop:</b> We don’t just impart skills but also want to make sure that you implement them post the course. We keep in touch with you via newsletters, webinars, and next-version training to assist you with this. Some post-training deliverables lined up for you are: </li>
                                                <li style="margin-left:25px;">Instructor-led session recordings</li>
                                                <li style="margin-left:25px;">Access to the alumni network</li>
                                                <li style="margin-left:25px;">Continued social learning with discussion forums, group messenger, and one-to-one messaging.</li>
                                                <li style="margin-left:25px;">Additional workshops on advanced level concepts</li>
                                                <li style="margin-left:25px;">Emails, blogs, articles, newsletters, tutorials, and other forms of rich informative material.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-4-5">5. What is KnowledgeHut’s approach to immersive learning?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-4-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-4">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Our <b>ITIL course</b> is characterized by its highly engaging, immersive learning environment. You get to learn, practice, assess, get insights on your learning, and personalize your learning journey. Many of our students have testified that KnowledgeHut provides the<b> best ITIL Certification</b> in the market. </p>
                                            <p><b>LEARN:</b> Self-learning videos, smart flashcards, interactive eBooks, and recall quizzes may all help you remember what you've learned. You may also use collaborative social learning, such as discussion forums and group and one-on-one texting, to increase your learning potential.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                            <p><b>PRACTICE:</b> Case studies and real-time simulations help you gain confidence and get productive from day one. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                            <p><b>ASSESS:</b> Assess your skills at every stage with a variety of questions ranging from multiple choice to code-based, completely auto-graded by the system. Micro "work-like" experiences are provided via assignments and projects inside our inbuilt and intelligent growth environment. Test your subject matter comprehension through diagnostic, module level, and final assessments.<br></p>
                                            <p><b>GET INSIGHTS:&nbsp;</b>You gain deep insights on your development based on your performance in exams, assignments, and projects, which help you identify areas where you excel and where you need to improve. All you have to do is follow the instructions and improve your skill level from where you are to where you want to be.</p>
