                                            <p>a) You need to earn 17 credits from the modules under ITIL® V3 scheme which makes you eligible to take the ITIL Managing Professional transition module in order to migrate to the ITIL® 4 scheme.<br></p>
                                            <p>b) Once you achieve the ITIL® 4 Managing Professional designation then you should also pursue the ITIL® 4 Strategic Leader. You can opt for ITIL 4 Master once you complete the modules under both the designations. AXELOS has introduced ITIL® 4 with a few new modules which you need to take up to become an ITIL® Master. Once you complete the ITIL 4 Foundation, you need to complete the modules under both the designations in order to become an ITIL® 4 Master.The ITIL® 4 modules recommended by AXELOS to become an ITIL 4 Master are as follows:<br><br></p>
