                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-6">6. What are the benefits of ITIL 4 Framework compared to ITIL® V3 Framework?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-6" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>ITIL 4 has been anticipated to solve the problem which was highlighted in ITIL V3 - the inability to keep up with the new technological advancements in the IT industry. Some of the benefits of ITIL 4 framework compared to ITIL V3 framework are-</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>It includes all the best things from ITIL</li>
                                                <li>It is flexible to work with other technologies and methods</li>
                                                <li>Provides a comprehensive approach for co-creating value for your customers</li>
                                                <li>Helps lay the course for the modern digital world</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>ITIL 4 Framework comprises of two key components, namely, ITIL® service value system (SVS) and the four dimensions model. The benefits of the newly introduced ITIL® Framework are as follows:</p>
                                            <ol>
                                                <li>The ITIL® SVS of the ITIL® Framework facilitates the integration and coordination of the components and activities which enables an organisation to create value through IT-enabled services.<br></li>
                                                <li>ITIL® SVS further provides a strong, unified, and value-focused direction for the organisation.<br></li>
                                                <li>An organisation can ensure its SVS remains balanced and effective by giving an appropriate focus on each of the dimensions under the four dimension model of the ITIL Framework.</li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-7">7. What is ITIL certification used for?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-7" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The certification is used to achieve quite a number of goals in the industry. Some of the benefits are:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>The <b>ITIL certification course</b> online increases the value of the professional in the labor market.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>It provides the platform to stand apart from the multitude of uncertified IT professionals in the industry.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>It is a medium for learning how to properly utilize ITIL tools and their techniques, improve efficiency and effectiveness at the workplace, and get recognized for your expertise by your peers both inside and outside the organization.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-8">8. How does ITIL help businesses?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-8" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Businesses who have adopted ITIL can vouch for its numerous benefits. Some of them include improved customer satisfaction, better communication flow, reduction in external and internal cost, business productivity and competent IT staff. ITIL, in short, helps businesses provide quality services. It also helps them manage business risks by preventing and resolving service disruption.<br></p>
                                            <p>ITIL has helped organizations improve the relationship they have with their clients.&nbsp; It brings your business alive because it ensures the software and hardware systems are all working in sync to enhance overall efficiency and productivity. ITIL is a framework that makes business activities easier, effective and efficient.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-9">9. Is it mandatory for me to complete all the modules under ITIL® 4 Managing Professional (ITIL® MP) and ITIL® 4 Strategic Leader (ITIL® SL) designations to become an ITIL® Master?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-9" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, AXELOS recommends that it is mandatory for you to complete all the modules under ITIL® 4 Managing Professional (ITIL® MP) and ITIL® 4 Strategic Leader (ITIL® SL) designations in order to become an ITIL® Master.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-10">10. How many PDUs will I be eligible for?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-10" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will get 16 PDUs.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-11">11. Why should I get ITIL certified?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-11" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The ITIL certification training course can benefit anyone who is interested in ITIL. It should be acquired for the following reasons:</p>
                                            <ol>
                                                <li>The certification will enable one to have a sound understanding of the ITIL® framework.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>It would assist those who have already adopted the ITIL® style to improve on their skill set in contributing to ongoing service improvement within the organization.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>It will help IT professionals enhance IT service management within the organization.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                                <li>It can help in acquiring the right skill set and qualifications needed for a chosen ITSM career</li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-12">12. Where are PDUs applicable?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-12" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>PDUs are credits awarded by the Project Management Institute. They recognize your dedication to the Project Management world through the award of credits for every educational effort you make throughout your career. PDUs are offered by the PMI®, and every PMI® certification, except the CAPM®, requires you to earn a specific number of PDUs per three-year certification cycle.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-13">13. How much does ITIL certification cost?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-13" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>There is no fixed cost of the ITIL certification. However, to determine the certification cost, two major components will have to be combined- the ITIL® exam cost and The ITIL® training cost. Other costs that are also included in the certification cost are the ITIL® study guide and the ITIL® practice tests. The ITIL Certification cost depends on some other factors and these would cause a variation in price, such as the mode of the exam to be taken and the country of residence.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-14">14. How much would an Instructor-led training for ITIL V4 Certification cost me in India, US and around the globe?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-14" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>India:</b> An instructor-led training for your ITIL V4 Certification would cost you roughly around <b>INR 19,999</b> in India.<br></li>
                                                <li><b>US:</b> Taking an instructor-led training for ITIL V4 Certification in the US would cost you around<b> $700.<br></b></li>
                                                <li><b>UK:</b> You can take an instructor-led training to get your ITIL V4 Certification by spending around <b>£925</b> in the UK.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-15">15. How much do I need to pay to avail classroom training for ITIL V4 Certification in India, US and around the globe?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-15" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Classroom training for <b>ITIL V4 certification</b> in India would cost you around <b>INR 19,999</b>. These training usually take place for 2 days. You need to spend around <b>$1,299</b> to take up classroom training for ITIL V4 certification in the US. Taking classroom training for ITIL V4 certification in the United Kingdom will cost you around<b> £465</b>. You can avail it from one of the leading training providers</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-16">16. Should I pay separately for the certification fee?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-16" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, your course fee includes the ITIL exam fee<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-17">17. What are the Key capabilities of ITIL?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-17" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Some of the key capabilities which&nbsp; ITIL® offers to organizations are:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Supporting all kinds of business outcomes</li>
                                                <li>Enabling business change</li>
                                                <li>Managing risk in line with the business needs</li>
                                                <li>Optimizing the customer experience&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Showing value for money</li>
                                                <li>Continually improving the services by learning from success/failures of past services</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-2-18">18. What is EXIN certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-2-18" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>EXIN is a renowned exam and certification institute that has certified millions of professionals in digital skills for tomorrow’s world. EXIN certifications assess and validate the competencies of professionals and organizations in different industry sectors across the world, and are in high demand.<br></p>
                                            <p>Popular EXIN programs include VeriSM™, Agile Scrum, DevOps, SIAM™, Information Security Management, Data Protection (based on GDPR), Cybersecurity, Data Center Management and Cloud Computing and e-CF® NEXT, among others.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="itil-4-foundation-exam">
                            <h3>ITIL 4 Foundation Exam</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="seo-content-accordion-3">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-3-1">1. What is the new ITIL V4 Exam Format?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-3-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The exam format for ITIL V4 is an objective test pattern with no negative marking. There are <b>40 questions</b> and you need <b>26 marks ( 65%) out of 40 to pass</b>. The duration is 60 minutes and it’s a closed book exam.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#seo-content-heading-3-2">2. What is the ITIL Exam Syllabus format and how to get certified in ITIL V3 Foundation?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="seo-content-heading-3-2" class="collapse" data-parent="#seo-content-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>In order to become an ITIL Foundation certified professional, one has to appear for the one hour online ITIL Foundation certification examination that is held on the last day of the training.</p>
                                            <p>The exam itself is a one-hour online examination comprising of 40 questions. You have to score 26 marks (65%) to attain the certification. You will be awarded 2 credits for the same.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
