            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle refers to the lifecycle approach to provide the best practice guidance for IT Service Management.The modules under ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle are relevant to those who intend to find a management or team leader role that requires management of different areas or work across different teams.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the purpose of ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The modules under the ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle category focus on the process and practice elements used, and the management capabilities needed in order to deliver quality Service Management practices.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the modules under ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The modules under the ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle are as follows:</p><ul><li>Service Strategy (SS)</li><li>Service Design (SD)</li><li>Service Transition (ST)</li><li>Service Operation (SO)</li><li>Continual Service Improvement (CSI).</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy under ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy is one of the five modules under ITIL® Service Lifecycle. It provides you with the guidance enabling you to develop, design, and implement service provider strategy that is aligned with the organisational strategy.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the purpose of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy under ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy module under the ITIL® V3 Service Lifecycle focuses on the importance of the strategic aspect of services within the IT service lifecycle. Further, it provides you with the specific knowledge and techniques in order to help you demonstrate the understanding of the risks and success factors and possess the skills to develop and progress strategy within an organisation and programme.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is covered under the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy course?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The course structure of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy module covers management and control of activities and techniques that are documented under the ITIL® Service Strategy publication, but it doesn’t provide full detail of each supporting process.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the cost of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy exam?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The cost of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy varies from country to country. You need to pay £283 towards the exam fee for ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy in India.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the key benefits of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The key benefits of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Service Strategy Certification are as follows:</p><ol><li><b>Formulate IT service strategy&nbsp;</b>by acquiring knowledge and management principles.<br></li><li><b>Provide vision and direction&nbsp;</b>for Service Management by getting the organisational capability.<br></li><li><b>Deliver value to the organisation&nbsp;</b>Getting a practical approach to moving an IT organisation from a focus on technology to a strategic approach in order to manage the Service Portfolio.</li></ol>"
            }
