            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How many credits do you earn on completion of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Continual Service Improvement module?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>You can earn 3 credits upon completion of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Continual Service Improvement module.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Who can take up the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Continual Service Improvement certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Intermediate Continual Service Improvement certification is suitable for the&nbsp; &nbsp;professionals:</p><ul><li>CIOs</li><li>CTOs</li><li>Business Relationship Managers</li><li>Cyber Resilience Consultants</li><li>Service Level Managers</li><li>IT Security Architects</li><li>Business Continuity Managers</li><li>IT Consultants</li><li>IT Audit Managers</li><li>Any IT professional involved in continual service improvement.</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is  ITIL® V3 Service Capability under the ITIL® V3 Intermediate certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Service Capacity updates you with the understanding of how different processes interact and their successful usage which plays an important role while understanding the ITSM frameworks. The ITIL® V3 Service Capability stream is divided into 4 modules that allow you to acquire and apply more specialized knowledge.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the purpose of ITIL® V3 Service Capability modules?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The purpose of the ITIL® V3 Service Capacity module is to get you equipped with specialized knowledge in one or more processes, with a focus on the day-to-day execution of ITIL® practices and the ways they interact.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the modules under ITIL® V3 Service Capability?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Service Capacity under ITIL® V3 Intermediate certification comprises of the following modules:</p><ul><li>Operational Support and Analysis (OSA)</li><li>Planning, Protection and Optimization (PPO)</li><li>Release, Control and Validation (RCV)</li><li>Service Offerings and Agreements (SOA).</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis module under ITIL® V3 Service Capability?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis (OSA) is one of the modules under ITIL® V3 Service Capability. It goes deep into the practical application of the OSA practices that enable event, incident, problem, request, technical, access, IT operations and application management.It also covers aspects in regards to people, procedures, relationships, and technology in order to ensure that the services provided under IT are of high quality and cost-effective as well as it meets organisational needs.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the purpose of  ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis module under ITIL® V3 Service Capability?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The purpose of ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis is to teach the organisations and individuals the ways to manage everyday operation of IT services and gain a better understanding of how to implement the ITIL® processes that will enable them to deliver and support the services provided to the customers.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does the course under ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis cover?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The content of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis course is based mainly on the best practice guidance contained in the ITIL® Service Operation publication.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the exam fee that I need to pay towards ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The exam fee for ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis certification in India is&nbsp; £283. However, the exam fee varies based on the country where you reside.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the key benefits of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The key benefits of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Operational Support and Analysis certification are as follows:</p><ol><li><b>Get more valuable skills&nbsp;</b>Get yourself equipped with a highly-demanded certification.<br></li><li><b>Learn OSA best practice&nbsp;</b>Equip yourself with the best practices in order to manage the everyday operation of IT services.<br></li><li><b>Deliver efficient services&nbsp;</b>Get an understanding of the ways to implement the ITIL® processes that will enable you to deliver and support services to the customers.</li></ol>"
            }
        }, {
