            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation module under ITIL® V3 Service Capability?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation is one of the four modules under ITIL® V3 Service Capability that focuses on the practical application of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation practices in order to enable to successful planning, testing, and implementation of new services that meet the needs of the organisation and users.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the purpose of  ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation module under ITIL® V3 Service Capability?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The purpose of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation module is to develop the understanding of ITIL® Service Transition processes among organisations or individuals while ensuring that the transitional changes are effectively managed, new services are validated and tested and that release and deployment fulfill organisational requirements. It further provides guidance on evaluating change and managing knowledge in order to improve decision-making processes.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does the content of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation course contain?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The content of the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation course consists of the best practice guidance contained in the Service Transition publication. The course is designed in order to develop an understanding of the ITIL® Service Transition processes across organisations or individuals.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the exam fee for  ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The exam fee for ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation changes from country to country. However, you need to pay £283 in order to sit for your ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation certification exam in India.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the benefits of taking the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The key benefits of taking the ITIL® V3 Intermediate Release, Control, and Validation are as follows:</p><ol><li><b>Get more valuable skills:&nbsp;</b>Add certification to your profile which is highly-demanded.<br></li><li><b>Learn RCV best practice:&nbsp;</b>Deliver services in order to meet the business needs by equipping yourself with the best practices.<br></li><li><b>Understand the processes:&nbsp;</b>Get a valuable understanding of the ITIL® Service Transition processes.</li></ol>"
            }
